EREN YANIK: Sure.

00:13:12.180 --> 00:13:12.862
ADI HADDAD: Can you
tell the audience

00:13:12.862 --> 00:13:14.125
a little bit about Gram Games.

00:13:14.125 --> 00:13:14.420
EREN YANIK: Sure.

00:13:14.420 --> 00:13:16.320
ADI HADDAD: What kind
of games do you have?

00:13:16.320 --> 00:13:18.450
EREN YANIK: So Gram
Games was primarily

00:13:18.450 --> 00:13:23.640
founded as a company that
makes quick games, make them

00:13:23.640 --> 00:13:28.320
fast, iterate fast, fail
fast, and then launch them

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:30.930
to the market separately,
with lean teams.

00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:34.950
That's why initially they
focused on ad based games,

00:13:34.950 --> 00:13:36.090
like hyper casual games.

00:13:36.090 --> 00:13:40.470
I think so far we have about
nine games in our portfolio.

00:13:40.470 --> 00:13:43.260
And eight of them
are close to fully ad

00:13:43.260 --> 00:13:47.040
funded, and hyper
