allocate your ad revenues

00:26:27.720 --> 00:26:29.720
into players, and
then compare if it

00:26:29.720 --> 00:26:32.277
leads to any
cannibalization or not,

00:26:32.277 --> 00:26:33.610
because this person watches ads.

00:26:33.610 --> 00:26:36.570
So that's why you go
with manual filters.

00:26:36.570 --> 00:26:38.730
You either filter the
number of videos they see,

00:26:38.730 --> 00:26:41.188
or the number of players that
are able to watch the videos.

00:26:41.188 --> 00:26:43.590
If they make a payment,
they take them out

00:26:43.590 --> 00:26:45.000
of the rewarded video.

00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:47.610
What we did was we capped
the number of videos

00:26:47.610 --> 00:26:49.340
that people can watch.

00:26:49.340 --> 00:26:53.500
And only capped it, I think,
at two per our players.

00:26:53.500 --> 00:26:55.580
That's why for us, and we
